  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Our Project staff, of only  women, provide orientation and education to 100 Dominican families with children and adolescents living with disabilities, through modelling and teaching, during weekly home visits and 2 weekly half-day group sessions for adolescents, to enhance their social and emotional development, independence skills and inclusion. The whole family will experience a better quality of life.</narrative>
